ty of dispatchable generators D(t) Demand profile (possibly stochastic) W (t) Weather input (for forecasting solar/wind) k Discrete-time index (if applicable)I. INTRODUCTIONR Ising energy demand, urgent need for decarbonization, increasing penetration of stochastic renewable energy sources (RES), and electrification of transport have necessitated the transformation of the traditional electric grid to an intelligent, adaptive, and sustainable smart grid.",
